<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-084-160  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 084 160.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Jan 15 1990 v7 n2 p50(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ASA to acquire maker of import-export software. (ASA InternationalLtd., Trade Data Services Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Johnson, Glen.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   ASA International Ltd. (acquisitions and mergers)Trade Data Services Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Ticker:    ASAA.andO;Topic:     MergerTurnkey SystemsImportExportSoftware PackagesSystem DevelopmentMarket Entry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ASA TO Acquire Maker of Import-Export SoftwareandM;WESTBOROUGH, Mass.--ASA International has agreed to acquire Trade DataServices of Schaumburg, Ill., for about $4.5 million.andM;Following completion of the deal, Trade Data's operations will be merged withthose of ASA's International Trade Systems (ITS) division in Salem, N.H.andM;Both Trade Data, which has been a subsidiary of International AdvisoryServices, and Asa's ITS division provide software and turnkey systems used bycustoms house brokers for importing and by freight forwarders for exporting.andM;ASA officials said the deal is significant because Trade Data's systems arebased on IBM platforms, whereas the ITS division's are based on DECplatforms.andM;For the first time, ASA officials said, the ITS division will be able tooffer potential clients the option of buying systems built by either of theworld's two largest computer companies.andP;  ASA will also benefit because theability to offer IBM equipment should open new sales avenues for its expandedITS division, the officials said.andM;&quot;We feel this will really give us an entry to [a market] that usually won'tcome to the table unless you can discuss IBM solutions,&quot; said DaveMargaretos, director of sales for ASA's ITS division.andM;No products that integrate the DEC and IBM platforms are planned, Margaretossaid, but the ITS division will be developing products that enhance existingTrade Data offerings.andP;  &quot;We view our VAX products as more complete andadvanced,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;We'll be looking to bring the IBM product up to thatlevel.&quot;andM;Both Trade Data and the ITS division have developed systems that allow forcollection of data needed to operate in the import and export business.andP;  Thesystems include programs that prepare government documents used in thatbusiness.andP;  They also perform electronic data dissemination.andM;The ITS division has had a 25 percent market share, and Trade Data has had a9 percent market share, ASA officials said.andO;</TEXT></DOC>